ORDER
PER CURIAM.
The order of the Commonwealth Court sustaining appellee’s preliminary objections to appellant’s complaint in mandamus and dismissing that complaint is affirmed. See Valley Forge Racing Ass’n v. State Horse Racing Comm., 449 Pa. 292, 297 A.2d 823 (1972).
JONES, former C. J., did not participate in the consideration or decision of this case.
